column523:
infected tooth extraction after several unsuccessful attempts to treat with antibiotics incl. 2 courses of penicillin, and 3 other stronger drugs I don't recall. After the extraction in April and subsequent bone graft in preparation for an implant, I needed vicodin or Tylenol #4 as needed in addition to 800mg ibuprofen and Tylenol extra strength three times a day. I also took Halcion before each of the two dental procedures.

I also had to take two different antibiotics for a urinary tract infection because the first one, Bactrim, was not one the organism was sensitive to. 

I also took Tylenol extra strength for headaches. I've had two ophthalmic migraines with bizarre sensory prodromes.

I dislocated my symphysis pubis last week and my chiropractor adjusted it. 

I have had some digestive trouble - diarrhea and belching. I also had some blood in my stools and some urinary stress incontinence.
